@startuml
skinparam style strictuml
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title US-11 Decode SDR to Value (Prediction Originates in Brain/HTM)

actor Developer
participant "InputHandler" as IH
participant "EncoderHandler" as EH
participant "Brain" as BR
participant "HTM / ColumnField" as HTM
participant "InputField" as IF
participant "RDSE / Scalar / Date / Category / Fourier Encoder" as ENC

Dev -> BR: step(inputs, learn=False)
activate BR
BR -> HTM: compute(learn=False)
activate HTM
HTM --> BR: predictive state
deactivate HTM

BR -> BR: prediction() uses predictive state
loop for each registered input field
  BR -> IF: decode("predictive")
  activate IF
  IF -> FE: decode(bit_vector, candidates)
  activate FE
  FE --> IF: decoded value + confidence
  deactivate FE
  IF --> BR: (value, confidence)
  deactivate IF
end

BR --> Developer: decoded output map + HTM state
deactivate BR

alt optional frequency-only preprocessing
  Developer -> IH: to_encoder_sequence(input_source, required_columns?, column?)
  activate IH
  IH -> IH: infer/sanitize sequence column + drop None
  IH --> Developer: sequence values
  deactivate IH

note over BR,HTM
Predictions are produced from Brain/HTM predictive state,
then decoded by InputField + encoder decode APIs.
end note
@enduml
